# Frontend Rules (Next.js 16 — client/)

## Server vs Client Components

```ts
// Server component (default — SSR, no hooks)
import { serverFetch } from "@/lib/server-fetch";
const data = await serverFetch<ProductList>("/products", { revalidate: 60, tags: ["products"] });

// Client component (needs interactivity/hooks)
"use client";
import { api } from "@/lib/axios";
const { data } = useQuery({ queryKey: ['products'], queryFn: () => api.get('/products') });
```

Server components by default. Add `"use client"` only when you need hooks, event handlers, or browser APIs.

## i18n — Locale-Prefixed URLs

All public paths are prefixed: `/en/products`, `/pl/blog`.

```ts
// Client components
const lp = useLocalePath();        // (path) => `/${locale}${path}`
const locale = useLocale();        // extracts locale from pathname

// Server components
import { localePath } from "@/lib/i18n";
import { cookies } from "next/headers";
const locale = (await cookies()).get("locale")?.value ?? "en";

// API calls — always pass locale
serverFetch(`/products?locale=${locale}`)
```

**Never hardcode locale in hrefs.** Always use `lp(path)`.

## API Types — Check Before Writing

Open `client/types/api.ts` first. Key gotchas:

| Type | Correct field | Wrong assumption |
|------|--------------|-----------------|
| `CartItem` | `product` (direct) | ~~`variant.product`~~ |
| `ProductVariant` | `attributes: Record<string,string>` | ~~`attribute_values`~~ |
| `ProductReview` | `author`, `body` | ~~`reviewer_name`~~ |
| `Order` | `items?.length` | ~~`items_count`~~ |
| `BlogPost` | `featured_image: string\|null` | ~~`cover_image_url`~~ |

## SEO

Every public page needs `generateMetadata()`:

```ts
export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  const product = await serverFetch<Product>(`/products/${params.slug}`);
  return {
    title: product.name,
    openGraph: { images: [product.og_image ?? product.thumbnail?.url] },
  };
}
```

Add JSON-LD: `<JsonLd data={buildProduct(product)} />` from `components/json-ld.tsx`.

## WCAG 2.1 AA — Required

- Icon-only buttons: `aria-label="..."` + `aria-hidden="true"` on icon
- Form inputs: `<label htmlFor="id">` or `aria-label`
- Active nav links: `aria-current="page"`
- Pagination nav: `<nav aria-label="Pagination">` + `aria-current="page"` on active
- Quantity updates: `aria-live="polite" aria-atomic` on the number
- Modal/dialog: focus trap (Tab/Shift+Tab inside), `role="dialog" aria-modal="true"`
- Skip link in root layout: `<a href="#main-content">Skip to main content</a>`

## Types in Separate Files

`.tsx` files are clean — **no `interface` or `type` definitions inside `.tsx`**.

```
ProductCard.tsx           ← component only
ProductCard.types.ts      ← Props + local types

components/cart/types.ts  ← types shared within the directory
types/api.ts              ← global API response types (check before writing)
```

```ts
// ProductCard.types.ts
export interface ProductCardProps { product: Product; showBadge?: boolean; }

// ProductCard.tsx
import type { ProductCardProps } from "./ProductCard.types";
```

## Key Dependencies

- TanStack Query for server state (client components)
- react-hook-form + Zod for forms
- Tailwind v4 with `dark:` prefix (`.dark` on `<html>`)
- `toast.success()` / `toast.error()` from react-toastify

